<TITLE> Strike hampers Ctg port operation </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Jan 12 (bdnews24.com)  A group of workers at Chittagong port went on strike on Tuesday to press for a nine-point demand halting cargo handling at four jetties. They demonstrated in front of Chittagong port building in the morning. But the port authorities said the workers' programme did not hamper much the port operation. CPA secretary Farhad Uddin told bdnews24.com: "The workers are engaged in loading and offloading goods in the container jetties. Due to the abstention loading and unloading have been affected concerning only few ships." The dock workers' association declared the work abstention programme on Monday to press the demands such as formation of Chittagong dock workers' governing board and reinstatement of the sacked workers. The workers said they would continue with their movement until their demands are met. b
